.Dd June 10, 2026
.Dt LIBCNOTIFY 3
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm libcnotify.h
.Nd Library to support cross-platform C notification functions
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In libcnotify.h
.Pp
Support functions
.nf
.Ft const char *
.Fo libcnotify_get_version
.Fa "void"
.Fc
.fi
.Pp
Stream functions
.nf
.Ft int
.Fo libcnotify_stream_set
.Fa "FILE *stream"
.Fa "libcnotify_error_t **error"
.Fc
.fi
.nf
.Ft int
.Fo libcnotify_stream_open
.Fa "const char *filename"
.Fa "libcnotify_error_t **error"
.Fc
.fi
.nf
.Ft int
.Fo libcnotify_stream_close
.Fa "libcnotify_error_t **error"
.Fc
.fi
.Pp
Verbose functions
.nf
.Ft void
.Fo libcnotify_verbose_set
.Fa "int verbose"
.Fc
.fi
.Pp
Print functions
.nf
.Ft int
.Fo libcnotify_printf
.Fa "const char *format"
.Va ...
.Fc
.fi
.nf
.Ft int
.Fo libcnotify_print_data
.Fa "const uint8_t *data"
.Fa "size_t data_size"
.Fa "uint8_t print_data_flags"
.Fc
.fi
.nf
.Ft int
.Fo libcnotify_print_error_backtrace
.Fa "libcnotify_error_t *error"
.Fc
.fi
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Fn libcnotify_get_version
function is used to retrieve the library version.
.Sh RETURN VALUES
Most of the functions return NULL or \-1 on error, dependent on the return \
type.
For the actual return values see
.In libcnotify.h .
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
None
.Sh FILES
None
.Sh SEE ALSO
.In libcnotify.h
